-- Euro-Area Construction Output Fell in November on France, Italy
-- B y   P a t r i c k   H e n r y
-- 2013-01-17T10:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-17/euro-area-construction-output-fell-in-november-on-france-italy.html
Euro-area  construction output  fell
in November as declines in France and  Italy  offset gains in
Germany and Spain.  Construction in the 17-nation euro area decreased 0.4
percent from October, when production was flat, the European
Union’s statistics office in Luxembourg said today. From a year
earlier,  output  declined 4.7 percent.  In Germany, Europe’s largest economy, November construction
advanced 1 percent from a month earlier, while Spain gained 1.2
percent, according to today’s report. In France and Italy,
output dropped 0.5 percent and 3.4 percent, respectively.  In the 27-nation EU, construction fell 0.9 percent from
October, when it rose 2.8 percent, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
